        <section class="glass-card p-6 space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-accent">BAND MEMBERS</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text/90">
            <h4>Viktória Šmídová</h4>
            <p><strong>Vocals, Production, Songwriting</strong></p>
            <p>Creates the vocal landscapes and lyrical content that define Lishkee's introspective character</p>

            <h4 class="mt-4">Radim Kocourek</h4>
            <p><strong>Production, Instrumentation, Songwriting</strong></p>
            <p>Handles instrumental composition, electronic production, and sonic experimentation</p>

            <p class="mt-4">Both members handle all aspects of their music production from their home studio in Brno, maintaining complete creative control over their artistic output.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="glass-card p-6 space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-accent">CREATIVE APPROACH &amp; PHILOSOPHY</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text/90">
            <p>Lishkee's creative process embodies the DIY spirit, with all music created, recorded, and produced in their small bedroom studio. This intimate setting allows for spontaneous experimentation and detailed sonic sculpting, resulting in music that feels both carefully crafted and organically evolved.</p>

            <p>The duo's willingness to experiment is evident in tracks like "Silver (Modular Version)," where modular synthesizers were recorded in a single take, embracing the unpredictability of the technology. This approach reflects their broader aesthetic: balancing control with chance, structure with improvisation, and electronic elements with human warmth.</p>

            <p>Their collaboration with visual artists (photographer Tomáš Škoda), filmmakers (Petr Kačírka), and theater collectives demonstrates a multidisciplinary approach that extends beyond traditional band activities into the realm of multimedia art.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="glass-card p-6 space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-accent">LOCATION &amp; SCENE</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text/90">
            <p><strong>Based in:</strong> Brno, Czech Republic</p>

            <p>Brno, the Czech Republic's second-largest city, has a thriving independent music and arts scene. The city is home to numerous cultural spaces, including the innovative Káznice community and cultural center where Lishkee has collaborated on theatrical productions. This rich cultural ecosystem has shaped Lishkee's artistic development and provided opportunities for experimental collaborations that blend music with visual arts, theater, and film.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

